  "original_title": "\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0db4\u0dd4 \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc2\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc3\u0ddd \u0d85\u0db6\u0dda\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Former Prime Minister Shinzo Abe was shot",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Foreign media reports that Shinzo Abe, a former Prime Minister of Japan, was shot and his condition is serious.",
        "The former Prime Minister was shot while attending a public meeting and addressing the gathering. It is reported that the shooting was done by an Irishman who was among the crowd and the security personnel immediately arrested him.",
        "Japan's NHK news service reports that the gunshots pierced the abbot's chest and his heart had stopped as he fell unconscious.",
        "Shinzo Abe is the longest serving Prime Minister of Japan. Abe, who held the position of Prime Minister from 2012 to September 2020, resigned from the post of Prime Minister, saying that he was unable to provide maximum service to the people due to his poor health."
      ],
